## Test Anti-Pattern Audit — `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 6 |
| **Medium** | 2 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called — achieving high line coverage — but almost nothing is actually *verified*. These tests will pass even if the production code is completely broken.

---

### 🔴 Critical Findings

#### 1. Systemic Coverage Touching (class-wide)

The entire test class methodically calls every public method with zero or trivial assertions. 6 of 10 tests have **no assertion at all**; the remaining 4 only assert `IsNotNull` — which for a `List<>` or non-nullable return will never fail.

**Affected methods (no assertion):**
- `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)
- `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 32)
- `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 39)
- `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)
- `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 69)
- `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 84)

**Affected methods (trivial `IsNotNull` only):**
- `GetProduct_Works` (line 23) — never checks SKU, Name, or Price
- `SearchProducts_Works` (line 46) — never checks count or content
- `GetAllProducts_Works` (line 55) — never checks count or content
- `ExportToCsv_Works` (line 77) — never checks CSV content

#### Concrete Fixes

**`AddProduct_Works` → verify the product is retrievable:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProductRetrievableBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
}
```

**`UpdatePrice_Works` → verify price changed:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesProductPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated?.Price);
}
```

**`RemoveProduct_Works` → verify product is gone:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_MakesProductUnretrievable()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}
```

**`SearchProducts_Works` → verify correct filtering:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
